<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She recently enjoyed a sun-soaked trip to Marbella. </p>

<p>And Chloe Ferry has certainly been busy since her return to the UK as she revealed she's now preparing to make her Newcastle mansion available to rent. </p>

<p>The Geordie Shore star, 25, took to Instagram on Monday to update her fans, joking that if anyone was keen for a stay they should 'get their offers in' soon. </p>

<p>Move on in! Chloe Ferry has revealed that her Newcastle home, which boasts a hot tub and games room, is going to be available to rent</p>

<p>Chloe explained that instead of permanently parting with the spacious abode when she moves to London, she had decided to put it on the market for rent.</p>

<p>She said: 'I have decided that I am going to move out of my house, so it is going to go on the market for rent. If anyone is interested then get your offers in! </p>

<p>'Just joking, but yeah my house is going on the market for rent… i've just moved into it as well.'</p>

<p>The beauty has regularly treated fans to glimpses inside her stunning house and even created a home account while she was redecorating.</p>

<p>Stylish: The Geordie Shore star's bathroom boasts white marble flooring and grey walls as well as a spacious tub </p>

<p>Perfect for parties: There is also a games room which has its own bar and art work on the walls</p>

<p>She moved into the space and started adding some fresh decorative touches in February after moving out of the place she shared with her ex Sam Gowland. </p>

<p>Since then Chloe has turned her house into a stunning pad, adding her own cinema and games room as well as a stylish outdoor space.</p>

<p>The abode boasts a grey and black marble theme with this being seen in the entertainment areas and bathroom.</p>

<p>Moving on: Chloe moved into the large home back in February and is now renting it out while she relocates to London</p>

<p>While the kitchen cupboards are a grey colour, perfectly complementing the white floors throughout the downstairs of Chloe's home. </p>

<p>Making sure there's space for all her stunning ensembles, Chloe has transformed one room into a dressing area with pink velvet chairs. </p>

<p>The stylish touches also continue outside as Chloe has had a grey seating area put in which makes the perfect space to rest after a dip in the hot tub. </p>

<p>And fans might recognise her eye-catching bathroom, which comes complete with a round tub, as Chloe often shares sultry selfies from there.</p>

<p>Work it: Chloe often shows off her sleek bathroom in sizzling selfies</p>

<p>Comfy: The beauty's bedroom also has lots of space and keeps with the stylish neutral design of the home</p>

<p>Little touches: The house also has some eye-catching lighting features in the white hallways </p>

<p>Speaking about her own space when she first moved in, Chloe said: 'What I really like about the house is it's got a lot of space when you walk in. I like the big rooms.' </p>

<p>During a series of videos shared to Instagram at the time the blonde beauty walked through the house before it was decorated.</p>

<p>She explained how she was hoping to transform the home into a stylish space and put down new carpets.</p>

<p>It comes after Chloe cried 'tears of happiness' as she thanked her followers for their support during her weight loss journey in an emotional Instagram clip in May.  </p>

<p>Quiet nights in: A living room at the home features a huge TV and cosy fire, perfect for the colder months</p>

<p>So chic! There's also a pretty dressing room complete with mirrored furniture and a pink velvet chair</p>

<p>Despite her transformation, the beautician recently admitted she still doesn't 'feel great' about her figure.</p>

<p>Chloe said the trolls have got 'inside my head' after being inundated with cruel taunts calling her 'fat and ugly every day'.  </p>

<p>The blonde recently enjoyed a trip to Marbella which came after she ignored speculation she had faked a trip to Ibiza and had instead secretly joined her ex Sam Gowland, 25, in Dubai.  </p>

<p>Enjoy it! Chloe has shared several snaps from inside her stunning home during lockdown</p>

<p>It had been reported that the star had back together with her co-star ex - despite being in the throes of filming Celebs Go Dating. </p>

<p>A source told The Sun the former-couple were said to be 'reconnecting'; but fans also connected the dots.</p>

<p>An insider said: 'Chloe's taking it really slowly and she's keen to keep it quiet as her friends will all be furious after all the drama. It's a chance for them to reconnect.'</p>

<p>Made up: Chloe decorated the whole house and put down new carpets and flooring during her renovations </p>
